Iberdrola Plans to Invest $2.16 Billion in New York by 2015, Europa Says

-- B y   M a n u e l   B a i g o r r i
-- 
2011-05-02T05:53:32Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-05-02/iberdrola-plans-to-invest-2-16-billion-in-new-york-by-2015-europa-says.html
The U.S. unit of Spanish power utility
 Iberdrola SA (IBE)  will invest $2.16 billion in the state of  New York 
between 2011 and 2015 to boost the business of NYSEG and RG&E,
the companies with which it operates in the area,  Europa Press 
reported, citing regulatory filings.  Of the total investment planned, $1.77 billion will be in
electricity generation and distribution and $397 million will be
in gas, the newswire said.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Manuel Baigorri at 
 mbaigorri@bloomberg.net 
To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Angela Cullen at 
 acullen8@bloomberg.net  